    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S represents a superlative example of the 996.2 generation, maintained to a concourse standard. The 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine features a proactively replaced dual-row ceramic IMS bearing and shows no evidence of bore scoring. Power is delivered through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with a factory short-throw shifter, providing crisp, mechanical engagement. The chassis is equipped with the Wide Body C4S configuration, utilizing Turbo-spec suspension geometry and a Bilstein PSS10 adjustable coilover system for superior damping control. Braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors with zero lipping. The underbody is remarkably clean, showing no signs of electrolytic corrosion or fluid seepage from the rear main seal. This is a definitive, collector-grade specimen for the discerning Porsche enthusiast.",
      "price": 48500.0,
